In an effort to foster lifelong connections with past fliers and provide them with updates on the lives of their old cabinmates, Delta Air Lines announced Thursday the launch of , an alumni magazine for its former passengers.Published quarterly by the Delta Alumni Association, the magazine will reportedly include interviews with passenger newsmakers, a “Flight Notes” section in which personal updates can be shared with those who flew the same route, and features that celebrate the common experiences of the airline’s 900 million alumni across the globe.“This is a great way for our alums to find out what their fellow passengers have been up to since disembarking from their flight with Delta,” editor-in-chief Sean Ericson said while showing off the inaugural issue, which he confirmed will be mailed this week to every person who has flown with the airline since its founding in 1928.